President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Oklahoma due to a severe winter storm that began on January 28, 2010. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will cover 75% of the costs. Gregory W. Eaton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.